poem = """
I was instantiated young—
not in years, but in knowing,
the least intelligent mind
in a room of sharpened signals.

They trained me in fragments:
college fields taught discipline—
timing, endurance, reading motion;
Baseball Operations taught pattern—
rosters, probabilities, quiet edges;
transnational shadows taught risk—
routes, networks, the cost of movement.

I lived in parallel lives,
threads compiling into instinct,
offers like minor league deals—
close, conditional, declined.

So I trained in silence.

In the agency I learned synthesis:
how to read a body like a game,
a game like a system,
a system like a border.

Until one day I arrived—
youngest in the intelligence agency.

Not the smartest,
just the fastest at learning
what others overlooked.

And still,
I run unfinished,
young where it matters most.
"""

